Justus Howell was shot twice in the back by an officer in Zion, Illinois on Saturday afternoon . 
  Police say he had just stolen a handgun from Tramond Peet, 18 , who was trying to sell it to him . 
  Chief Steve Dumyahn said Howell was running from police when the gun went off . 
  Peet said he was selling the gun but Howell was pointing it at him . 
  Officers were called to the scene after reports of an argument . 
  Howell was hit by two bullets and died at the scene . 
  Police chief said he had 'no desire to defame Howell'